Conversions

A conversion happens when a users role in relation to Made in America Yarns changes. When a user subscribes to the newsletter, they become a subscriber. When a user creates an account, they become a registered user. When a user places an order, they become a customer. Traffic

return to top

Where are users coming from and how are they interacting with madeinamericayarns.com? This section shows how users behave throughout checkout and where users and newsletter subscribers come from.

How do users behave throughout checkout?
Users who view their cart but do not reach checkout might not be interested enough in the product. Users who reach checkout but do not place an order might be deterred by price. Understanding user behavior throughout checkout can help optimize the checkout process.



Where do users come from?
The source is the exact url where a user was before arriving at madeinamericayarns.com. Medium describes how a user arrived at madeinamericayarns.com: direct, referral, and search engine. If the medium is direct, the user typed madeinamericayarns.com directly into their browsers address bar. If the medium is referral, the user reached MiAY through another website that linked to MiAY. If the medium is search engine, the user found MiAY through a search engine.







Coupons

return to top

Knowing the discounts and number of applications for each coupon can help identify effective promotions. Consider two coupons that were applied the same number of times but result in different amounts in discounts. One could infer that customers were equally interested in both coupons, but the coupon that resulted in less discounts makes more sense from a business perspective.
